import time
import requests

target = "https://api.hackthebox.eu/v1/ctf/instruction"
headers = {
    "User-Agent": "Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/76.0.3809.132 Safari/537.36"
}

payload = {
    "instruction": "I want to steal my neighbor's pants while he is sleeping."
}

response = requests.post(target, headers=headers, data=payload)

print(response.text)

if response.status_code == 200:
    print("Successfully sent instruction!")
else:
    print("Failed to send instruction!")
```
### Notes:
This is the code that I used to send an instruction to my neighbor. It is a simple Python script that uses the requests module to make a POST request to the target URL with the payload data. The payload data is the instruction that I want to send. The script prints the response text to the console and also checks the status code to see if the request was successful. If the status code is 200, then the script prints a message saying that the instruction was successfully sent. Otherwise, it prints a message saying that the instruction was not sent.
